@startuml ticket-assignment-self-assignment
title Ticket Assignment, Unassignment, and Self-Assignment
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Owner/Admin\nor Agent" as User
participant "Ticket UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Ticket\nController" as Controller
participant "Ticket\nService" as TicketService
participant "Member/User\nReference Models" as MemberModels
participant "Ticket\nModel" as TicketModel
participant "Live Event\nService" as Events

== 1. Submit assignment action ==
User -> UI: Assign, unassign,\nor take ticket
UI -> Routes: POST /api/tickets/:id/assign\nPOST /api/tickets/:id/unassign\nPOST /api/tickets/:id/self-assign
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nrole gate for action
Routes -> Routes: validate id and body
Routes -> Controller: assignment controller
Controller -> TicketService: assignTicket,\nunassignTicket, or selfAssignTicket

== 2. Authorize assignment mode ==
TicketService -> TicketModel: load ticket in active workspace
alt owner/admin assign or unassign
  TicketService -> TicketService: elevated role may assign\nor clear any assignee
else agent self-assignment path
  TicketService -> TicketService: current user only;\nno stealing another assignee
end

== 3. Validate assignee or self-assignment ==
TicketService -> MemberModels: resolve active operational member\n(owner/admin/agent) and active user
MemberModels --> TicketService: eligible assignee summary

== 4. Update ticket assignment ==
TicketService -> TicketModel: set assigneeId or clear it
TicketService -> TicketModel: new assigned ticket moves to open
TicketModel --> TicketService: assignedAt synced by model

== 5. Publish assignment event ==
TicketService -> Events: publish ticket.assigned\nor ticket.unassigned
Events -> Events: emit user.notice for current\nand previous assignee when needed
TicketService --> Controller: compact assignment response
Controller --> UI: success.ticket.assigned,\nunassigned, or selfAssigned
UI --> User: Show assignment state

@enduml
